 water, threatened above all by periodical flooding. In the short twentieth century, this was something with which both cities had to deal constantly. This study focuses on the cities’ management strategies, which were influenced by specific local factors such as urban development as well as overarching political and economic conditions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFloodszGermanyzMannheimxHistoryy20th century. 4a20. Jahrhundert. 4aKatastrophenbewältigung. 4aKrisenprävention. 4aStadtgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aThiessen, Nadja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG0 cEPUBz97831107347060 cprintz978311073854440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311073467640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110734676423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110734676/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023